A R E S O L U T I O N
In memory of Mary Rose Oakar.
WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio were deeply saddened to learn of the passing of Mary Rose 2
Oakar and extend our heartfelt condolences to her family and friends; 3
and 4
WHEREAS, Mary Rose Oakar left an indelible impression on the 5
people whose lives she touched, and she will be remembered as a 6
spirited individual who contributed immeasurably to the world around 7
her. Widely renowned for her prolific career in public service, she 8
served three years on the Cleveland City Council and then sixteen 9
years in the U.S. House of Representatives serving Ohio’s 20th 10
District, where she was instrumental in supporting legislation 11
affecting women’s and elder issues, government employees, Social 12
Security, and fair compensation as well as securing resources for the 13
revitalization of downtown Cleveland and the surrounding area, and she 14
was the first Democratic woman from Ohio, Arab-American woman, Syrian- 15
American, and Lebanese-American woman to be elected to this position. 16
She went on to be sworn in to the Ohio House of Representatives and 17
then to hold the posts of member of the Ohio State Board of Education 18
and president of the American-Arab Anti-Discrimination Committee. 19
Indeed, she will be remembered for her generosity, talents, and 20
seemingly inexhaustible energy; and 21
WHEREAS, Mary Rose Oakar was an educator at Lourdes Academy and 22

